ANNAY.definition: to moan or cry because of pain, to express pain, to say ouch.
ANNAY.eng_example: You are good in expressing pain.
ANNAY.ilok_example: Nalaing ka la unay nga agannay.

ANNONG.definition: to be able, competent or qualified to do or carry.

ANNONG.ilok_example: Saan ko nga maannongan dayta ta nadagsen.

ANNUGOT.definition: to obey; to consent to, to acquiesce, permit.
ANNUGOT.eng_example: Don’t acquiesce that it is your fault.
ANNUGOT.ilok_example: Saan mo nga annuguten nga basol mo.

ANNUGOT.eng_example: Pepe is willing to do the dishes.

ANNUROT.definition: to acquiesce, consent, agree; to comply, obey.

ANNUROT.ilok_example: Umannurot kan tapno awan ti riri.

synonyms: (dial.) NANA. see AN-ANO, INTONANO, KANNO, KAPIN-ANO

ANTA.definition: to soak, immerse, Iyantam dayta dita danum tapno nadardaras nga maikkat ta rugit na.

ANTIGO.definition: of good quality, genuine, not an imitation.

ANUD.definition: to carry away: said of water currents.
ANUD.eng_example: Don’t drop your shoes for it might be carried away by the currents of this river.
ANUD.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ibbatan dayta swekos mo ta dinto iyanud toy karayan.

ANUD.definition: to be carried away by water currents.

ANUP.definition: to hunt wild animals usually with dogs and guns or bows and arrows and spears.
to hunt usually with dogs and guns, or bows and arrows and spears.
ANUP.eng_example: We’ll go and hunt a wild pig.

ANUS.definition: patient, kind, gentle, considerate, lenient, indulgent, forbearing.
to be patient, kind, gentle, etc.
to be patient with, to be kind to, to endure, suffer (someone or something).
ANUS.eng_example: Be kind to your mother and father for they are already weak.
ANUS.ilok_example: An-anusara ta nanang ken tatang mo ta nakapsut dan.

AON.definition: to come up, climb up, as from a hole, a canal, etc.

AON.ilok_example: Adu ti alinta nga immaon idiay kanal.

AON.definition: to pull up from, to push out from, to take out from, to scoop from.

AON.ilok_example: Inda iyaon diay ubing nga natnag idiay adalem nga abut.

AP-AP.definition: a piece of cloth, paper, leaf, etc. that is spread on the floor, ground, table, bed, etc.
to spread a piece of cloth, paper, leaf, etc. on (the floor, the ground, a table, a bed, etc.).

AP-AP.definition: to spread on, to use as spread.

APAGKANITO.definition: in a short time, in a moment.

APAS.ilok_example: Saan ka nga makiangaw no nalaka ka nga maapas.

APAY.ilok_example: No malagip ko ni nanang ko, umapay ti iliw ko.

APGES.definition: sharp, acute, smarting: said of pain.

APIG.definition: to part: said of the hair, grasses, underbrush, etc.

APIN.definition: any leaf or pieces of leaf, usually of the banana, spread at the bottom of an earthen pot before the rice that has to be cooked is poured into it.
to place this at the bottom of a pot.
to place this at the bottom of.
APIN.eng_example: Spread a leaf at the bottom of the pot first then pour in the rice.
APIN.ilok_example: Apinam nga umuna ta banga sa mo ipisok diay bagas.

APIRAS.definition: to grope, search by feeling; to feel with the hand.
APIRAS.eng_example: Feel with your hand the surface of the table.

APIRING.definition: to stay or stand close or adjacent to, to cling to.
to be close to each other almost or actually touching one another.
APIRING.eng_example: Put that seat near the wall until they are close to each other.
APIRING.ilok_example: Iyasideg mo dayta tugaw dita pader inggana ti agapiring da.

APIRING.definition: to put, place or take close to.

APLAT.definition: a kind of aphid or plant louse.

APLIT.definition: to whip in a slashing way.
APLIT.ilok_example: Saan mo nga aplitan dayta asok.

APLIT.definition: to whip (someone or something) in a slashing way.
APLIT.eng_example: Don’t go near that crocodile lest he slashes his tail on you.
APLIT.ilok_example: Saan ka nga umasideg ti dayta buaya ta dinanto ket iyaplit ta ipus na kenka.

APNUT.definition: to wax; said of strings, threads, etc.
APNUT.eng_example: Wax the sewing thread so that it will become strong.

APO.definition: a respectful term of address used to an older man or woman, or a person of authority; (sir, ma’am) may be followed by the surname of the person or the title of his or her position.

APO.cross_reference: TI TUMENG, great-grandparent, great-grandchild. TI DAPAN, great-great-grandparent, great-greatgrandchild

APON.definition: to roost: said especially of fowls.
to put in a roost, to roost.

APONG.definition: grandparent, grandfather, grandmother; may be used as a term of address.

APOY.definition: to produce or give off sparks, to spark or sparkle.
APOY.eng_example: The big knife which he hit that big stone with gave off sparks.
APOY.ilok_example: Immapoy diay buneng nga intagbat na idiay bato.

APOY.definition: to cook rice, to cook a meal.
APOY.eng_example: Cook the meal now for I am already hungry.

APOY.definition: to cook (rice or the food for a meal).

APPOPO.definition: to become or be shaped like a cup: said of the hands.

APPUT.definition: to cover one’s external genitals with one’s hands.
to cover, screen off with one’s hands.
APPUT.eng_example: Cover your eyes with your hands.

APRAD.eng_example: This is the one which causes me to become hoarse.
I don’t like that for it causes hoarseness.

APRANG.definition: horrible, horrid, dreadful, terrible, shocking, ghastly.

APRAS.definition: to beat, to strike with a stick, pole, etc. so as to drop down.
APRAS.eng_example: Strike the fruits of the mango with a stick so that they will drop down.
APRAS.ilok_example: Aprasem dagita bunga ti mangga tapno matnag da.

APROS.definition: to touch, rub or stroke softly and gently with the hand.

APSAY.definition: to sit down with the legs stretched out.

APUNGOL.definition: to embrace, hug; to clasp in one’s arms.

AR-ARAK.definition: bait, anything used as a lure, enticement.
to entice or lure to do something.
AR-ARAK.eng_example: Entice that hen so that it will lay many eggs.
AR-ARAK.ilok_example: Ar-arakam dayta manok tapno adu ti iyitlogna.

ARAB.eng_example: Don’t allow those goats to graze in our yard.
ARAB.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ipalubos nga agarab dagita kalding ditoy inaladan tayo.

ARADAS.definition: to go stealthily and rape a sleeping woman.
to go to (a woman) stealthily and rape.

ARADO.definition: to plow, to use a plow.

ARADO.definition: to plow, to use a plow on.

ARADO.ilok_example: Inka man aradoen diay talon ko.

ARAGAAG.definition: old, such as utensils, tools, etc.

ARAGAN.definition: an edible, brown seaweed or alga with flat thallus. ; IMMARAGAN,

ARAKIAK.definition: to cackle, to cry: said of hens and roosters.

ARAKUP.definition: to embrace, hug, clasp with both hands.

ARAMANG.definition: a kind of small, edible, marine shrimp.

ARANG.definition: to block, blockade; to obstruct; to ambush, Isuda ti nangarang kaniak.
ARANG.ilok_example: They were the ones who ambushed me.

ARAPAAP.definition: to dream of, imagine, aspire for.

ARARAW.eng_example: There are many who beg him for work.
ARARAW.ilok_example: Adu ti umararaw kenkuana iti trabaho.

ARARAWAN.definition: an edible, soft-winged insect that lives in wet places.

ARAS.definition: a disease of the mouth of children and occasionally of adults characterized by pearl-colored flakes.

ARASAAS.definition: to whisper, to say or tell in a whisper.

ARASAW.definition: water used in washing or rinsing rice.
to wash or rinse husked rice.
to wash or rinse in water.

ARAYAT.definition: to go and help, to give aid.

ARBAAKA.definition: an aromatic plant used as a diuretic and to facilitate menstruation.

ARBAS.ilok_example: Saan mo pay nga arbasan dayta nga kayo.

ARBIS.definition: to be caught in a drizzle or light rain.

AREM.definition: to court or woo a girl.

AREM.ilok_example: Saan mo nga armen dayta kasinsin mo.

ARENG-ENG.definition: to neigh, whinny; to whine, moan.

ARENG-ENG.ilok_example: Kasla ka la al-alia nga agar-areng-eng dita suli.

ARI.definition: to become supreme, to be king.

ARIBASAY.definition: to ooze, leak, trickle, flow out.

ARIBUNGBUNG.definition: to surround, encircle, gather around, throng around.

ARIBUNGBUNG.ilok_example: Saan yo nga aribungbungan dayta masakit.

ARIEK.definition: to be tickled, excited or stirred up agreeably.

ARIKAP.definition: to grope for, frisk for, feel with the hand.

ARIKAP.ilok_example: Arikapem tay tulbek ko dita tuktok ti aparador.

ARIMEKMEK.definition: to make a noise or sound, to be noisy.

ARIMPADEK.definition: to walk heavily or noisily, to stamp the feet.
ARIMPADEK.eng_example: Don’t stamp your feet because someone is sleeping.
ARIMPADEK.ilok_example: Saan ka nga agarimpadek ket adda matmaturog.

ARIMUKAMOK.definition: to drizzle lightly, to rain lightly.

ARIN-.definition: ; ARIN--EN, AR-ARIN--EN ± R2, adjectivizing affixes meaning: to seem what the stem implies.

ARINSAYAD.definition: to trail, as a skirt or a pole carried on the shoulder.

ARINSAYAD.ilok_example: Ingatom dayta pandiling mo tapno saan nga agarinsayad.

ARINUNOS.definition: the latter period (of), the terminal period (of), the period toward the end (of).

ARINUNOS.ilok_example: Arinunos ti Disiembre idi naawat ko diay surat mo.

ARIPAPA.definition: to calm down, to tone down, to pipe down.

ARISIT.definition: to pour off gently into a container in order to remove the sediments or dregs of.

ARIT.ilok_example: Saan mo ar-ariten dayta ub-ubing ngem sika.

ARITOS.eng_example: She does not like to wear earrings.

ARITOS.definition: to put on (someone) or wear as earrings, to use as earrings.

ARIWEKWEK.definition: to abound, teem; to be abundant, plentiful, numerous.

ARNAS.definition: to glean, to pick up bit by bit.

ARSANG.definition: to snuff (e.g. a candle), to remove the ash of (e.g. a cigarette).

ARTAP.ilok_example: Saan na nga maartapan ti kinabaknang ti karruba na.

ARTYUK.definition: to tease, provoke, incite; to humor.

ARTYUK.ilok_example: Ar-artyukem ni nanang mo tapno igatangan na ka ti badom.

ARUYOT.ilok_example: Agar-aruyot ti dara idiay sugat na.

ARWAT.definition: to use, especially personal things; to wear.

ARWAT.ilok_example: Ania ti arwatem nga mapan idiay eskuela?

ASAWA.definition: to get married to, to marry with.

ASAWA.ilok_example: Kayat na kano ti makiasawa kaniak.

ASAWA.ilok_example: Mapan ko iyasawa daytoy balasang ko idiay Manila.

ASIDEG.ilok_example: Urayen nak idiay asideg ti simbaan.

ASIDEG.definition: near, close (in time and space); approaching.

ASO.definition: to set on, urge on, to offer or suggest as wife or husband, partner, etc.

ASPING.definition: to be similar to, to resemble.

ATINGAW.eng_example: Don’t walk or run without looking for you might be run over by a vehicle.
ATINGAW.ilok_example: Saan ka nga agat-atingaw ta dikanto ket maatalan.

ATIPA.definition: to stop, block, obstruct, impede, hinder.

ATIPOKPOK.definition: to fly, float, to be blown (e.g. papers, dust, etc.).
ATIPOKPOK.eng_example: Don’t open that window so that these papers won’t fly.
ATIPOKPOK.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ilukat dayta tawa tapno saan nga agatipokpok dagitoy papel.

ATIR.definition: to arrange side by side, e.g. pieces of wood.

ATONG.definition: firebrand, a log that burns the whole day, or the whole night.

ATOR.eng_example: Straighten your back. 2. to correct, rectify, amend, Isu ti nangator ti kinasukir na.

ATROS.definition: a kind of ghost that is supposed to be blown about by the wind bringing sickness or death to anyone that it touches.

ATSUETE.definition: a shrub with burry fruit whose red seeds are used for coloring.

AW-AW.eng_example: The water in the jar spilled out.

AW-AWAN.definition: to baffle, deceive, confuse; to mislead; to cause to be lost, go astray or be misled; to cause (worry, problems, etc.) to disappear.
to be lost, confused, misled; to disappear (such as worries, problems, etc.). see under AWAN.

AWA.definition: to preserve or protect against, to keep away from (injury, illness, misfortune, etc.).

AWAG.eng_example: The mayor proclaimed the new law.
AWAG.ilok_example: Inyawag ni mayor ti baro nga linteg.

AWAN.definition: as a particle it indicates: 1. the non-existence or absence of someone or something.
AWAN.eng_example: There is nobody in the house. 2. the non-possession of something by someone.

AWAN.definition: to be deprived of, to be lacking or wanting of, to run out.

AWANAN.definition: deprived of, bereft of, dispossessed of; lacking or wanting for, in need of.
AWANAN.eng_example: They are here again, those bereft of shame.
AWANAN.ilok_example: Adda da manen dagiti awanan ti bain.

AWAT.eng_example: Hand over to him his change.
AWAT.ilok_example: Iyawat mo kaniana diay suppli na.

AWAT.eng_example: I don’t understand what you are saying.

AWAT.definition: able to understand or comprehend things.

AWAY.definition: any place outside the town proper; field, barrio, sitio.

AWAY.eng_example: We are going to the field tomorrow.

AWENG.definition: to resound, reverberate, to produce a sonorous or echoing sound.

AWER.definition: to roar: said of the ocean, river, wind, etc.

AWID.eng_example: He does not want to go home anymore.

AWID.definition: to bring or take or carry home.
AWID.eng_example: Bring home some vegetables which we will cook into a vegetable dish.
AWID.ilok_example: Mangiyawid ka ti nateng nga dengdengen tayo.

AWID.definition: to pull back or toward oneself.
AWID.eng_example: Pull that chair back here. ; SANGKAAWID,

AWID.definition: one twenty-fifth of a skein of a hand of cotton yarn.

AWIR.definition: to take care of, look after (a child or a baby).
AWIR.eng_example: Take care of this child for I have to go somewhere.
AWIR.ilok_example: Awirem daytoy ubing ta adda papanak.

AWIS.definition: to invite, urge to go; to attract, allure, move, entice.

AWIS.eng_example: The aroma of this coffee is inviting.
AWIS.ilok_example: Makaawis ti ayamoom ti kape nga itoy.

AWIT.eng_example: Will you please carry my suitcase?

AY.definition: auxiliary and intransitive verb: to come.
an exclamation expressing disgust mixed with wonder.

AY-AYAM.definition: 1. game, sport, play, recreation, diversion, amusement.
AY-AYAM.eng_example: What game is that? 2. toy, plaything.
They won’t play with me. see under AYAM.

AYA.definition: an interrogative word with the added notion of wonder.

AYAB.eng_example: The lady teacher is calling you.

AYAM.definition: to play with, toy with, amuse oneself with.

AYAM.eng_example: Don’t open that basket lest the crabs crawl out.
AYAM.ilok_example: Saan mo nga lukatan dayta kuribot ta dinto agayam dagita kappi.

AYAN.eng_example: Their house is in a clear place.
AYAN.ilok_example: Napannayag ti ayan ti balay da.

AYAT.eng_example: Do you think she will accept my love?
AYAT.ilok_example: Awaten na ngata ti ayat ko?

AYAT.definition: to like, love, want to; to take delight or pleasure in (doing something).
AYAT.eng_example: It is he who wants us to go. 2. to love, like, want, desire.
AYAT.ilok_example: Isu ti agayat nga mapan kami.

AYAT.eng_example: The spinster is fond of you.
AYAT.ilok_example: Naayat diay baket nga balasang kenka.

AYEK-EK.definition: to laugh in a suppressed manner, to titter, to giggle.

AYNA.definition: an exclamation expressing wonder and admiration.

AYO.definition: to comfort, soothe, pacify, cheer up.
AYO.eng_example: He is comforting the lady who is crying.
AYO.ilok_example: Ay-ayoen na daydiay balasang nga agsangsangit.

AYO.definition: object or cause of one’s comfort or pleasure, what one is fond of.

AYON.definition: to agree with, side with, favor, approve, to incline toward.
AYON.eng_example: Don’t agree with that deed of his.
AYON.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ayonan dayta aramid na.

AYOS.definition: to be carried by the current, to be flown away.
to be carried by the current, to be flown away.
AYOS.eng_example: My shoes were carried away by the current in the brook.
AYOS.ilok_example: Naiyayos diay sapatos ko idiay waig.

AYUG.definition: accent, manner of speaking or pronouncing; intonation; tempo.

AYUNGIN.definition: a kind of small, blackish fish which is edible.

AYWAN.definition: to watch, look after, attend to, take care of, guard.
AYWAN.eng_example: Watch over your brother (or sister) for I am going somewhere.
AYWAN.ilok_example: Aywanam dayta kabsat mo ta adda la papanak.
